{{Use British English|date=August 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} '''Thomas Sherrer Ross Boase''', [[Military Cross|MC]], FBA (1898&ndash;1974) was a British [[art historian]], university teacher, and [[Vice-Chancellor of the University of Oxford|Vice-Chancellor]] of [[Oxford University]].<ref>Stoye, John, ‘[http://www.oxforddnb.com/index/101030830/ Boase, Thomas Sherrer Ross (1898–1974)]’, ''[[Oxford Dictionary of National Biography]]'', September 2004. {{DOI|10.1093/ref:odnb/30830}}.</ref><ref>Alexander, Jonathan J., ‘[http://www.rhs.ac.uk/bibl/xSearch.asp?DATABASE=dcatalo&rf=200004090 Thomas Sherrer Ross Boase, 1898–1974]’. ''[[Proceedings of the British Academy]]'', 101:353–364 (1999), . {{ISSN|0068-1202}}.</ref>
==Life==
Thomas Boase was born in [[Dundee]], [[Scotland]], and was educated at [[Rugby School]] in [[England]] (1912–17). He fought on the [[Western Front (World War I)|Western Front]] during [[World War I]] in the [[Oxford and Buckinghamshire Light Infantry]] (1917–19) and was awarded the [[Military Cross]]. Boase studied [[Modern History]] at [[Magdalen College, Oxford]], from 1919–21, and was subsequently Fellow and Tutor at [[Hertford College, Oxford|Hertford College]] from 1922–37.
From 1937–47, Boase was Director of the [[Courtauld Institute of Art]] in [[London]] and Professor of [[History of Art]] at the [[University of London]].<ref>[http://courtauld.ac.uk/about/history History of the Courtauld], ''The Courtauld Institute of Art''.</ref> During [[World War II]], he worked in the [[Government Code and Cipher School]] at [[Bletchley Park]], followed by the [[RAF]] in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]], from 1939–41. He was then in charge of [[British Council]] activities in the [[Middle East]], also based in Cairo, from 1943–45.
From 1947–68, Boase was [[Colleges of the University of Oxford#Heads of Houses|President]] of Magdalen College. He also served as Vice-Chancellor of Oxford University from 1958–60.
He was [[Slade Professor of Fine Art]] at Oxford for 1963–64.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hoa.ox.ac.uk/fileadmin/hoa/documents/pdf/Oxford_Slade_Professors.pdf|title=Oxford Slade Professors, 1870–present|publisher=University of Oxford|date=2012|accessdate=27 January 2015|format=PDF|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213123228/http://www.hoa.ox.ac.uk/fileadmin/hoa/documents/pdf/Oxford_Slade_Professors.pdf|archivedate=13 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Boase became a Fellow of the [[British Academy]] in 1961. He was a Trustee of the [[National Gallery, London|National Gallery]] (1947–53) and the [[British Museum]] (1950–69). He was also a member of the Advisory Council of the [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] (1947–70).
